cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a heuristic algorithm for Model-based Bayesian Reinforcement Learning (BRL) and analyzes its sample complexity. It also involves experimental results to highlight the key differences of this method compared to previous work, which is a common practice in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as BRL is a subfield of AI that deals with decision-making in uncertain environments. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as BRL has applications in robotics and control systems. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper introduces a new algorithm for BRL and analyzes its performance.
